(Kabira 1984) where I argued for greater recognition of the artist. <#/>The general argument at t
he time was that an artist takes the liberty to deal with the motif at hand and it is important to look at the kind of details the individual adds: the words he/she chooses, the authorial voice, the narrator's comments, and how she/he brings conflicts to 
resolutions, among others. <#/>These ideas still hold but in this chapter a new dimension is added to the analysis.
\par }\pard\plain \s94\qj\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \f16\lang1031 {\f0\lang2057 <h> <#/>}{\b\f0\lang2057 The Gender dimension and the story teller}{\f0\lang2057  </h>
