desert territory. <#/>Hence, settlers occupied close to 50 per cent of all the arable land or up to 20 per cent of the most fertile land in the country. <#/>Conflict over what came to be known as the stolen lands and the subsequent shortages of land culmi
nated in the outbreak of the Mau Mau war for liberation, 1952-1956. <#/>In the mean time, the colonial government's refusal to address itself to the root cause of the problem\emdash land shortage\emdash 
